23/01/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The EU External Relations Council on Monday (January 22nd) approved the European Partnership with Montenegro tool, which outlines short- and medium-term priority tasks in Montenegro's EU integration process. 
The EU foreign ministers called for the efficient implementation of the set measures, reaffirming its willingness to assist in the effort. 
The Council's endorsement came as the first EU-Montenegro Troika meeting was held in Brussels between Montenegrin Foreign Minister Milan Rocen and his counterparts from the countries representing the former, the current and the future EU presidency. 
(Vijesti - 23/01/07; EU website, Mina - 22/01/07)
